\begin{abstract} This note establishes  that  a generalization of $c$-cyclical monotonicity from the Monge-Kantorovich problem with two marginals gives rise to a sufficient condition for optimality also in the multi-marginal version of that problem. To obtain the result, the cost function is assumed to be bounded by a sum of integrable functions. The proof rests on ideas from martingale transport.\\ 
\noindent\emph{Keywords:}   cyclical monotonicity, mass transport. \\
\end{abstract}



