\begin{theorem}
Let $c$ be a continuous cost-function $E \rightarrow [0, \infty)$ which is bounded  by a sum of integrable functions. Let  $\mu$ be a $c$-monotone transport plan in $\cM (\mu_1, \dots, \mu_d)$. Then $\mu$ is optimal. 
\end{theorem}

